\begin_layout Standard
Stan passed on the borsht and instead made his way to the pantry.
 His wrinkled nose gave away the fact that the smell put him off.
 Sergei shrugged and dug in heartily, though rather noisily.
 Miki and Elaine were sitting at one table, playing a rather convoluted
 version of chess, involving dice and an imaginary toroidal chessboard.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They were heavily absorbed, and didn't take notice of Stan eating away at
 the snacks they'd brought with them from their last trip south: goat's
 cheese and garlic bread from France, and smoked salmon from Finland.
 They didn't even notice when Stan sat down next to them, pretending to
 watch while stuffing himself shamelessly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bjorn entered the small but comfy mess room, all red-faced and smiling.
 Sousuke followed close behind, his thermo in hand and a sore look on his
 face.
 Stan took notice and asked after swallowing a mouthful:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

What's with Takahashi?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bjorn gave a shrug and made his way to the toilet, while Sousuke ignored
 Stan and vanished in the small kitchen.
 Stan downed another bite of cheese before talking to practically none other
 than himself:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

What's with everyone? Not enough snow? Too much white in your day? What
 is it this time?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sergei looked up from his meal, shrugged and happily continued sipping his
 soup being a little more mindful of those around him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I spilled his tea!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 came Bjorn's muffled shout.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

All of it?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, asked Stan leaning back on his chair.
 Elaine momentarily raised her head searching for the source of the small
 raucus, but gave no sign it was about to ruin her game.
 Miki took Elaine's knight, smiled and announced her victory:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Checkmate.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Elaine cursed and looked at the chessboard befuddled, before asking rather
 haplessly:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

No? No way out? If I..
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

No.
 Checkmate,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 repeated Miki, barely shaking her head and asked:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Did you eat all the cheese?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There was a confused look written across her features, pointing at Stan
 with an accusing finger.
 Stan licked his lips and looked at the ceiling mischievously.
 Elaine buried her face in her palms, her voice quite heartless:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Merdre..
 Three times in a row.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bjorn came out of the toilet, his work suit unzipped, hanging around his
 waist like a peeled banana.
 He said then with a lot of sarcasm but just a touch of genuine concern:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Isn't it strange that a quarter of the world's thorium stock relies on a
 bunch of geeks with a lot of time, a lot of money, and little in the way
 of spending either?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sousuke came out of the kitchen holding a sword.
 An unsheathed sword.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Stan was the first one to exclaim:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Wow! A real-life samurai.
 Just like in those old movies.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bjorn looked a little curious when he asked:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Isn't that the antique you brought in last time? What was the name for -
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His sentence was cut in half, as was his throat.
 Jets of blood sprayed Sousuke as he mercilessly and efficiently cut down
 each and every one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sergei was still trying to smash through a window when Sousuke's blade severed
 his spine.
 Stan tried to put up a fight with a shovel that happened to be lying around
 but his one swing never connected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sousuke on the other hand, was flawless - like a machine; Stan's head rolled
 off his spine like it had been fake all along.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Elaine found out that the door had been locked from the inside - everyone
 had been too absorbed to notice.
 Her wound was clean, through the heart; a small mercy of sorts.
 Miki sat frozen still at the table, clutching at the chessboard.
 It happened; even some animals never fled - accepting the inevitable, seeing
 through the falseness of their instincts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Her evolved brain though had to know, so she asked, with tears running down
 her face, amidst sobs and silent, muffled cries:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Why? Whatever the reason, why?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Because I hate you, Miki.
 I hate the whole world.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

But-
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Her voice died abruptly in her throat with a horrible gurgling sound.
\end_layout

